  "prompt": "Is it too late to start a computer science degree if I am 20 and don't know any programming languages?",
  "response": "It's definitely not too late to start a computer science degree at 20! Here are some encouraging points:\n\n1. Advantages of starting at 20:\n- You're mature and likely more focused\n- You have life experience\n- You're still very young in terms of career potential\n- Many successful programmers started later\n\n2. Learning curve:\n- Most CS programs start from the basics\n- No prior programming knowledge is usually required\n- First-year courses teach fundamental languages and concepts\n\n3. Preparation tips:\n- Try free online coding tutorials (Codecademy, freeCodeCamp)\n- Watch YouTube programming tutorials\n- Practice basic coding before starting your degree\n- Consider intro programming courses\n\n4. Career prospects:\n- Tech industry values skills over age\n- Computer science offers diverse career paths\n- Good salaries and job opportunities\n- Constant learning is part of the field\n\n5. Alternative paths:\n- Coding bootcamps\n- Online degrees\n- Self-learning with certifications\n- Associate degrees before bachelor's\n\nThe most important factors are:\n- Passion for learning\n- Dedication\n- Consistent practice\n\n20 is still very young in the tech world. Many successful programmers started in their 20s or even 30s. Don't let age discourage you from pursuing your interests.",
